QuarkSketch — Test Cases
TC01 — Main menu loads
Open index.html in browser. Expected: logo, Single Player, Multiplayer, Leaderboard and Settings buttons are visible.
TC02 — Single Player navigates to canvas
Click Single Player. Expected: drawing screen appears with a white canvas and tool sidebar.
TC03 — Drawing works with mouse
On the canvas, click and drag. Expected: a black line follows the cursor.
TC04 — Drawing works on touch
On a touch device, press and drag on the canvas. Expected: a black line follows the finger.
TC05 — Back button returns to menu
On the canvas screen, click the back arrow. Expected: main menu is shown again.
TC06 — Settings panel opens and closes
Click Settings on the main menu. Expected: settings panel appears. Click Close. Expected: panel disappears.
TC07 — Dark mode toggle
Open Settings and flip the dark mode switch. Expected: background changes to dark. Flip it back. Expected: returns to light.
TC08 — Portrait warning on mobile
Open the app on a phone in portrait mode. Expected: rotate device message is shown and the menu is hidden.
